"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkinformationtoolbench=globalThis.webpackChunkinformationtoolbench||[]).push([[8863],{3833(n){n.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"itb-0.0.7","metadata":{"permalink":"/docs/changelog/itb-0.0.7","source":"@site/changelog/master/2026-02-25-itb-0.0.7.md","title":"ITB 0.0.7","description":"We\'re thrilled to announce the release of ITB 0.0.7, a comprehensive update combining enhanced WebApp capabilities with advanced API functionality.","date":"2026-02-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"itb-0.0.7","title":"ITB 0.0.7","authors":[],"tags":[]},"unlisted":false},"content":"We\'re thrilled to announce the release of **ITB 0.0.7**, a comprehensive update combining enhanced WebApp capabilities with advanced API functionality.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## \ud83d\udce6 Release Overview\\n\\nThis release bundles improvements across components and infrastructure:\\n\\n| Component | Version | Focus |\\n|-----------|---------|-------|\\n| **WebApp** | 0.0.7 | 10 UI/Model features + 1 bug fix |\\n| **API** | 0.0.7 | Metadata tracking & version tracking |\\n| **Infrastructure** | 0.0.7 | Traefik load balancer + integrated docs container |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83c\udfaf WebApp 0.0.7\\n\\n**8 UI Features & 2 Model Improvements**\\n\\n### Highlights\\n\\n- \u2728 **Model Filter by Entity Type** - Focus on relevant entity types\\n- \u2728 **Add Entity to Canvas Center** - Improved entity placement\\n- \u2728 **Entity Usage Indicators** - See where entities are used across viewpoints\\n- \u2728 **Edge Highlighting** - Trace relationships at a glance\\n- \u2728 **Attribute Drawer** - CTRL+4 for quick attribute access\\n- \u2728 **Save Canvas as Image** - Export documentation\\n- \u2728 **Auto Arrange Canvas** - Optimize layout automatically\\n- \u2728 **Resizable Left Sidebar** - Flexible workspace\\n- \ud83c\udf81 **Mandatory Attribute Field** - Better data modeling\\n- \ud83d\udc1e **Fixed Edge Routing** - Proper visualization on collapse\\n\\n\u2192 [View WebApp 0.0.7 Release Details](/changelog-webapp/webapp-0.0.7)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\ude80 API 0.0.7\\n\\n**Enhanced Traceability & Version Tracking**\\n\\n### Highlights\\n\\n- \ud83d\udccb **Metadata Export File** - Automatic `_metadata.json` with version info and statistics\\n- \ud83d\udd0d **`/pb_info` Endpoint** - Query PocketBase version information\\n\\n**What\'s tracked:**\\n- ITB frontend, API, and library versions\\n- Export timestamp\\n- Entity, relation, viewpoint, and node counts\\n\\n\u2192 [View API 0.0.7 Release Details](/changelog-api/api-0.0.7)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83c\udf93 Summary\\n\\nITB 0.0.7 represents a significant milestone with improved usability, better model traceability, and enhanced data quality practices. The WebApp gains powerful productivity tools while the API adds comprehensive version tracking for compliance and diagnostics.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \u26a0\ufe0f Major Changes & Migration Guide\\n\\n### \ud83d\udd04 Environment Configuration Changes\\n\\nThe `.env` file has been updated with new configuration options. **Action Required:**\\n\\n1. **Backup your current `.env` file:**\\n   ```bash\\n   cp .env .env.backup\\n   ```\\n\\n2. **Update to the new `.env` template:**\\n   ```bash\\n   cp .env.example .env\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Re-apply your custom settings** from the backup file to the new `.env`\\n\\n**Key changes:**\\n- New Traefik load balancer configuration variables\\n- Updated image tags for version 0.0.7\\n- New documentation container settings\\n\\n### \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Architecture Updates\\n\\n#### 1. **Traefik Load Balancer (NEW)**\\n\\nThis release introduces **Traefik** as a local load balancer, providing a cleaner URL structure for development:\\n\\n**Local Access URLs:**\\n- **WebApp:** `http://itb.localhost` (instead of port-based URLs)\\n- **API:** `http://api.itb.localhost` (instead of port-based URLs)\\n- **Traefik Dashboard:** `http://traefik.localhost:8080` (optional monitoring)\\n\\n**Why this helps:**\\n- Simplified development URLs\\n- Closer alignment with production architecture\\n- No need to remember port numbers\\n- Supports multiple projects running simultaneously\\n\\n**Setup:**\\nYour `/etc/hosts` file should include (already configured if using provided docker-compose):\\n```\\n127.0.0.1 itb.localhost\\n127.0.0.1 api.itb.localhost\\n127.0.0.1 traefik.localhost\\n```\\n\\n#### 2. **Integrated Documentation Container (NEW)**\\n\\nThe ITB documentation is now packaged as an integrated container service running **busybox with httpd** webserver:\\n\\n**Access Documentation:**\\n- Access directly: `http://itb.localhost/docs`\\n- Documentation is fully functional without external network calls\\n\\n**Benefits:**\\n- Documentation always matches your deployed version\\n- Offline-friendly within your local/internal network\\n- No external dependencies\\n- Consistent documentation across teams\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udccb Update Instructions\\n\\n### For Existing Users\\n\\nFollow these steps to upgrade to ITB 0.0.7:\\n\\n1. **Backup your data:**\\n   ```bash\\n   # Backup the current model\\n   save remote in the WebApp to export the Model to JSON\\n   Backup your Output / JSON Folder\\n   ```\\n\\n2. **Update your environment:**\\n   ```bash\\n   # Stop current instance\\n   docker compose down\\n\\n   # Pull latest itb version from GitHub\\n   git pull\\n   \\n   # Backup and update .env\\n   cp .env .env.backup\\n   cp .env.example .env\\n   # Re-apply your custom settings\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Pull latest images and start:**\\n   ```bash\\n   docker compose pull\\n   docker compose up -d\\n   ```\\n\\n4. **Verify the installation:**\\n   - WebApp: `http://itb.localhost`\\n   - API: `http://api.itb.localhost`\\n   - Docs: `http://itb.localhost/docs`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \ud83d\udd27 Troubleshooting\\n\\n### Issue: Containers not starting or old configuration persists\\n\\nIf you encounter issues after upgrading, try the following steps to perform a clean start:\\n\\n#### Option 1: Clean Restart (Recommended)\\n\\n**Stop and remove all containers:**\\n```bash\\n# Stop all running containers\\ndocker compose down\\n\\n# Verify no ITB containers are running\\ndocker ps | grep itb\\n# (should return no results)\\n```\\n\\n**Remove the PocketBase data volume (\u26a0\ufe0f This will reset your database):**\\n```bash\\n# List volumes to find pb_data\\ndocker volume ls | grep pb_data\\n\\n# Remove the volume\\ndocker volume rm itb_pb_data\\n# (or adjust the name based on your project folder name)\\n```\\n\\n**Start fresh:**\\n```bash\\ndocker compose up -d\\n```\\n\\n#### Option 2: If you need to preserve your data\\n\\n**Stop containers but keep volume:**\\n```bash\\ndocker compose down\\n```\\n\\n**Then restart with the existing data:**\\n```bash\\ndocker compose up -d\\n```\\n\\n#### Common Issues & Solutions\\n\\n| Issue | Solution |\\n|-------|----------|\\n| **Traefik routes not working** | Ensure `/etc/hosts` has `127.0.0.1 itb.localhost api.itb.localhost` entries |\\n| **Port already in use** | Run `docker ps` to check conflicts and stop conflicting containers |\\n| **Documentation not loading** | Verify docs container is running: `docker ps \\\\| grep docs` |\\n| **API not responding** | Check logs: `docker compose logs api` |\\n| **Can\'t access PocketBase UI** | Default URL is `http://localhost:8090/_` (note: uses localhost, not traefik hostname) |\\n\\n#### Full Reset (Last Resort)\\n\\nIf issues persist, perform a complete reset:\\n\\n```bash\\n# Stop everything\\ndocker compose down\\n\\n# Remove all ITB-related containers\\ndocker ps -a | grep itb | awk \'{print $1}\' | xargs docker rm -f\\n\\n# Remove volume\\ndocker volume rm itb_pb_data\\n\\n# Clean up any dangling images (optional)\\ndocker image prune -a\\n\\n# Start fresh\\ndocker compose up -d\\n```\\n\\n> **\u26a0\ufe0f Warning:** This will permanently delete your PocketBase data. Make sure you\'ve exported your models first!\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Thank you to all contributors and users who made this release possible!**"}]}}')}}]);